[snoring]

02:13.840 --> 02:15.080
Bilkey.

02:15.200 --> 02:16.280
Hm.

02:16.400 --> 02:18.000
You're doing that thing again.

02:18.120 --> 02:19.440
Oh, geez.

02:19.560 --> 02:20.560
Sorry, mate.

02:20.680 --> 02:23.080
Three mornings in a row.

02:23.200 --> 02:25.160
Yeah, sorry, sorry.

02:25.280 --> 02:26.200
Need a slash, eh.

02:28.880 --> 02:31.760
You'd make someone abloody good wife, Bilkey.

02:31.880 --> 02:33.120
You say that every morning.

02:33.240 --> 02:36.320
And I mean it every morning.

02:36.440 --> 02:38.520
So what's the take, Ted?

02:38.640 --> 02:41.480
Not too shabby indeed.

02:41.600 --> 02:43.160
So are we done, do you reckon?

02:45.960 --> 02:47.960
I wouldn't mind getting back toCarol, if you know what I mean.

02:48.080 --> 02:51.720
One more on the way home.

02:51.840 --> 02:53.160
Martha?

02:53.280 --> 02:55.360
Not Martha.

02:55.480 --> 02:56.640
We're driving through Wyee.

02:56.760 --> 02:58.320
No, not bloody Martha.

03:01.320 --> 03:03.080
You know my reasons
why, so drop it.

03:03.200 --> 03:04.920
So I did.

03:05.040 --> 03:08.840
I was thinking that jewelersin Hamilton look pretty tasty.

03:08.960 --> 03:11.480
Nice to pick up a
trinket for the ladies.

03:11.600 --> 03:12.880
This isn't you.

03:16.000 --> 03:18.200
Most of the time, no.

03:18.320 --> 03:20.840
No, I mean here.

03:20.960 --> 03:24.200
Mrs. Suburban Housewife.

03:24.320 --> 03:26.400
I'm much more than that.

03:26.520 --> 03:29.280
Are you?

03:29.400 --> 03:30.160
You could be.

03:35.800 --> 03:36.680
[knock on door]

03:36.800 --> 03:38.440
What?

03:38.560 --> 03:40.440
Is Auntie Pat awake yet?

03:40.560 --> 03:42.280
Not quite, love.

03:42.400 --> 03:43.640
You said we
could play cricket.

03:43.760 --> 03:44.840
Soon.

03:44.960 --> 03:46.240
But you promised.

03:46.360 --> 03:49.240
Wolf, go outside and play.

04:05.320 --> 04:07.680
Hey.

04:07.800 --> 04:08.800
Who are you?

04:08.920 --> 04:10.080
Wolf.

04:10.200 --> 04:13.920
Wolf, like a dog.

04:14.040 --> 04:15.520
What kind of name is that?

04:15.640 --> 04:17.600
Wolves aren't dogs.

04:17.720 --> 04:19.320
It's short for Wolfgang.

04:19.440 --> 04:20.200
Who are you?

04:20.320 --> 04:21.440
Maria.

04:21.560 --> 04:22.480
We just moved in.

04:25.440 --> 04:27.520
Why are you hitting the tree?

04:27.640 --> 04:29.600
Because I hate it.

04:29.720 --> 04:30.880
This would be a
really good lawn if it

04:31.000 --> 04:32.800
wasn't for this stupid tree.

04:32.920 --> 04:34.200
So get rid of the tree.

04:34.320 --> 04:36.480
Can't.

04:36.600 --> 04:37.680
Why not?

04:37.800 --> 04:39.480
Uh, it's too big.

04:39.600 --> 04:41.400
I could pull it out.

04:41.520 --> 04:43.080
Bet you couldn't.

04:45.920 --> 04:48.000
Is this your son?

04:48.120 --> 04:49.360
Who are you?

04:49.480 --> 04:51.400
[inaudible] from
down the road.

04:51.520 --> 04:53.120
And what's your problem?

04:53.240 --> 04:54.680
Your son.

04:54.800 --> 04:57.360
He is animal.

04:57.480 --> 05:00.080
My family bring this treefrom Dalmatia when we come

05:00.200 --> 05:02.000
to work on your oil refinery.

05:02.120 --> 05:03.960
When we moved to Oakland,we replanted the tree

05:04.080 --> 05:05.960
in our new home, as a symbol.

05:06.080 --> 05:07.360
And now--

05:07.480 --> 05:09.160
Stick it back in
the bloody ground

05:09.280 --> 05:10.960
if you're that worried about it.

05:11.080 --> 05:12.320
[MUSIC - CITIZEN BAND, "RUST IN MY CAR"]

05:12.440 --> 05:13.800
[SINGING] Like rust in my car.

05:13.920 --> 05:16.600
You hold the thing together.

05:16.720 --> 05:18.640
Were you showing
off for that girl?

05:22.240 --> 05:23.920
Your father will deal withyou when he gets back.

05:24.040 --> 05:25.000
When, in three years?

05:25.120 --> 05:25.960
Go.

05:26.080 --> 05:26.840
Out of my sight.

05:32.120 --> 05:34.080
Did you get a hiding?

05:34.200 --> 05:35.520
No.

05:35.640 --> 05:36.920
Bet you did.

05:37.040 --> 05:37.880
No.

05:46.920 --> 05:50.240
See you at the shindig.

05:50.360 --> 05:51.240
Hey, son.

05:51.360 --> 05:55.880
I'll tell Mum you're here.

05:56.000 --> 05:57.200
Mum, Dad's home.

06:02.640 --> 06:03.480
Darling.

06:03.600 --> 06:06.040
Hello, love.

06:06.160 --> 06:07.440
You should've called.

06:07.560 --> 06:09.680
I would have made
myself presentable.

06:09.800 --> 06:13.640
Oh, you look more thanpresentable to me, my love.

06:13.760 --> 06:15.360
Mind you, I've been
sharing a van with four

06:15.480 --> 06:16.800
blokes for the last two weeks.

06:16.920 --> 06:18.680
You silver-tongued fox.

06:25.000 --> 06:25.760
Pat.

06:25.880 --> 06:26.760
Hello, Ted.

06:26.880 --> 06:28.680
Didn't know you were here.

06:28.800 --> 06:32.240
I just popped down to giveRita a hand while you're away.

06:32.360 --> 06:33.600
That's good of you.

06:33.720 --> 06:35.080
How was the trip?

06:35.200 --> 06:36.880
It was productive.

06:37.000 --> 06:39.400
You can hear all about ittonight when the lads are over.

06:39.520 --> 06:40.760
Of course.

06:40.880 --> 06:44.080
For now, you and I have
some catching up to do.

06:44.200 --> 06:45.960
I should really getthings ready for the party.

06:46.080 --> 06:47.840
No, that can wait.

06:47.960 --> 06:48.720
Excuse us, Pat.

06:48.840 --> 06:49.800
Won't be long.

06:49.920 --> 06:50.680
As I recall.

06:54.440 --> 06:57.920
Can we play cricket now?

06:58.040 --> 06:58.800
Sure.

07:14.280 --> 07:15.360
Wolfie.

07:15.480 --> 07:16.280
Wolfie!

07:16.400 --> 07:18.040
Come here, love.

07:18.160 --> 07:20.000
Would you be a darling
and get your Auntie

07:20.120 --> 07:23.360
Ngaire another drink, andCarol and Janet too, please.

07:23.480 --> 07:24.920
Just-- we're drinking
screwdrivers.

07:25.040 --> 07:26.840
Just a little bit of voddy,some orange, and some ice,

07:26.960 --> 07:28.040
all right, sweet heart?

07:28.160 --> 07:29.000
Oh, you're a good boy.

07:35.240 --> 07:37.120
You'll have to
lock him up, Rita.

07:37.240 --> 07:38.000
Maybe I will.

07:38.120 --> 07:38.920
He'll be running riot.

07:44.600 --> 07:46.280
You gotta go get that.

07:46.400 --> 07:47.880
- What?
- You gotta go get it.

07:48.000 --> 07:48.840
That's the rules.

07:48.960 --> 07:52.480
No, it is when [inaudible]

07:59.360 --> 08:03.200
And we hunted,
and we gathered.

08:03.320 --> 08:07.120
And now we bringofferings for our ladies.

08:07.240 --> 08:10.320
Janet, I saw
this and the color

08:10.440 --> 08:11.640
really sets off your eyes.

08:11.760 --> 08:12.760
Oh my god, Bilkey.

08:18.480 --> 08:20.200
You're the bloody
light of my life, Carol.

08:23.600 --> 08:25.080
Jesus, Phineas.

08:29.920 --> 08:31.880
My sweet.

08:32.000 --> 08:37.120
[GASPS] Lefty, oh my god.

08:43.200 --> 08:44.440
For you, my love.

08:49.280 --> 08:51.360
It's beautiful.

08:51.480 --> 08:52.240
Thank you.

08:56.360 --> 08:57.720
Never mind, Bert.

08:57.840 --> 08:59.560
One day there will be alady to receive your gifts.

08:59.680 --> 09:02.000
Yeah, sure.

09:02.120 --> 09:04.560
And now, we dance
like Cossacks.

09:04.680 --> 09:07.680
No, I'm not bloodycelebrating that little pig

09:07.800 --> 09:08.800
and his four innings.

09:10.480 --> 09:13.320
Why does that bitch deservesomething that beautiful?

09:13.440 --> 09:15.320
I bet she lets Leftystick it wherever he wants.

09:18.280 --> 09:19.120
Oy, oy.

09:19.240 --> 09:20.120
What's this?

09:20.240 --> 09:23.520
[tense music playing]

09:23.640 --> 09:24.440
Shit.

09:27.720 --> 09:30.520
Can I help you there?

09:30.640 --> 09:31.480
Her.

09:31.600 --> 09:34.120
I need word with.

09:34.240 --> 09:35.920
So you brought along
all these people?

09:36.040 --> 09:37.480
I have heard from
the people around here

09:37.600 --> 09:38.640
what your are kind are.

09:38.760 --> 09:39.760
New Zealanders.

09:39.880 --> 09:40.840
What the fuck are you?

09:40.960 --> 09:43.760
[laughing]

09:43.880 --> 09:44.640
What's the problem?

09:44.760 --> 09:46.480
She knows.

09:46.600 --> 09:48.600
Some Dallie tart
was leading my boy on.

09:51.360 --> 09:52.160
Come on.

09:52.280 --> 09:53.360
Do it.
Oh, yeah.

09:53.480 --> 09:54.880
We will.
- Good.

09:55.000 --> 09:56.400
I haven't had a
decent fight in eons.

09:56.520 --> 09:57.840
Hey!

09:57.960 --> 09:58.520
Hey, hey, hey, hey, hey!No one's gonna fight, OK?

09:58.640 --> 09:59.160
Not at my party.

10:01.920 --> 10:04.720
What is it you actually want?

10:04.840 --> 10:06.720
The tree that was destroyed.

10:06.840 --> 10:08.080
It must be replaced.

10:08.200 --> 10:09.200
You can plant another one.

10:09.320 --> 10:10.320
Nothing to do with us, bitch.

10:10.440 --> 10:11.240
Rita.

10:11.360 --> 10:14.240
Not helping.

10:14.360 --> 10:15.520
Let me get to the
bottom of this,

10:15.640 --> 10:17.680
and I'll come talk to you.

10:17.800 --> 10:18.640
You live down the road right?

10:18.760 --> 10:19.600
I've seen you around.

10:19.720 --> 10:20.800
Mm.

10:20.920 --> 10:22.040
Tomorrow, OK?

10:22.160 --> 10:23.000
We can sort it.

10:23.120 --> 10:23.880
Tomorrow.

10:39.320 --> 10:40.280
[snickering]

10:40.400 --> 10:41.200
Why?

10:41.320 --> 10:42.160
Why do this?

10:42.280 --> 10:44.040
She dared me.

10:44.160 --> 10:45.480
Who cares?

10:45.600 --> 10:47.760
You never commit a crimeunless you profit from it.

10:47.880 --> 10:50.400
Never.

10:50.520 --> 10:52.920
And profit in a moneysense, not in a "She might

10:53.040 --> 10:55.440
let me touch her tits" sense.

10:55.560 --> 10:58.800
And also, do not get caught.

10:58.920 --> 11:00.520
That is rule one.

11:00.640 --> 11:02.960
Dad got caught.

11:03.080 --> 11:04.560
I'm talking about you.

11:04.680 --> 11:06.200
This girl is trouble.

11:06.320 --> 11:09.200
Stay away.

11:09.320 --> 11:12.040
And also-- if you're goingto steal a girl jewelry,

11:12.160 --> 11:15.920
get her a necklace everytime-- not a fucking broach.

11:16.040 --> 11:17.440
You don't like
what Dad got you?

11:17.560 --> 11:21.200
A broach says "old lady"and necklace says "taste."

11:21.320 --> 11:23.200
It's not your father's
fault he has none.

11:23.320 --> 11:24.120
Wolf can finish those.

11:24.240 --> 11:25.000
Come to bed.

11:37.760 --> 11:40.000
Why do you always have
to be "Mr. Reasonable?"

11:40.120 --> 11:42.160
Why do you always pick fights?

11:42.280 --> 11:44.240
It's a bloody tree.

11:44.360 --> 11:45.600
Why should we care about them?

11:45.720 --> 11:47.440
Because we have to
live in the same street.

11:47.560 --> 11:49.640
So?

11:49.760 --> 11:51.680
You know, it's like thebloody Pakis and [inaudible]

11:51.800 --> 11:52.840
you went to war with.

11:52.960 --> 11:53.840
You weren't the
one at home all day,

11:53.960 --> 11:57.280
smelling their bloody cooking.

11:57.400 --> 11:58.920
I want a job.

11:59.040 --> 12:00.200
What's that got
to do with the tree?

12:00.320 --> 12:01.720
Because I am sick
of being the one

12:01.840 --> 12:03.320
that has to deal
with all this shit.

12:03.440 --> 12:05.560
By "all this shit," doyou mean raising our son?

12:05.680 --> 12:08.320
He's old enough to
look after himself.

12:08.440 --> 12:10.840
I need something to do, Ted.

12:10.960 --> 12:16.200
Give me something else to do,so I won't get into fights.

12:16.320 --> 12:20.880
[heavy breathing]

12:21.000 --> 12:24.160
Well, we could always
have that second kid

12:24.280 --> 12:26.960
we've been talking about.

12:27.080 --> 12:30.920
[music playing]

12:59.080 --> 13:00.720
Ted.

13:00.840 --> 13:01.840
You're back.

13:01.960 --> 13:03.480
Back from where?

13:03.600 --> 13:04.840
You tell me.

13:04.960 --> 13:05.720
Nope.

13:05.840 --> 13:07.440
Not a clue.

13:07.560 --> 13:09.080
I haven't seen
you for a while.

13:09.200 --> 13:10.960
Jeez, you must be prettybloody useless at looking

13:11.080 --> 13:12.480
because I've been right here.

13:12.600 --> 13:14.720
Well, here or work.

13:14.840 --> 13:17.640
Work didn't happen to take youto Tokoroa or Tauranga, did it?

13:17.760 --> 13:19.560
I don't like Tokoroa.

13:19.680 --> 13:21.080
It smells funny.

13:21.200 --> 13:22.480
What about Hamilton?

13:22.600 --> 13:24.040
Word comes down the
line there's some

13:24.160 --> 13:27.000
elegantly-crafted robberies.

13:27.120 --> 13:30.600
I think to myself, I haven'tseen Ted West lately.

13:30.720 --> 13:32.000
Wish I could help
you, Mr. McArthy.

13:32.120 --> 13:33.440
I really do.

13:33.560 --> 13:35.120
You wouldn't be
helping me, Ted.

13:35.240 --> 13:39.360
You'd be helping yourself downthe straight and narrow path.

13:39.480 --> 13:42.280
Whatever path it is, it didn'ttake me to any of those towns

13:42.400 --> 13:43.880
you're talking about.

13:44.000 --> 13:46.200
RITA: And I can testify to that.

13:46.320 --> 13:47.800
Sure you can, Rita.

13:47.920 --> 13:49.960
Been real
stay-at-home, we have--

13:50.080 --> 13:52.280
watching the election
hoo-ha on the telly.

13:52.400 --> 13:54.040
Is that so?

13:54.160 --> 13:55.680
Which side of the
fence you on, Ted?

13:55.800 --> 13:57.680
Oh, my blood runs red.

13:57.800 --> 13:59.480
Citizen Verolling, that's me.

13:59.600 --> 14:00.680
I like Muldoon.

14:00.800 --> 14:02.000
Won't deny it.

14:02.120 --> 14:03.920
Tell you, Mike, our
political differences--

14:04.040 --> 14:05.240
some nights it's a
wonder the neighbors

14:05.360 --> 14:06.680
don't call the police.

14:06.800 --> 14:08.040
Fair enough.

14:08.160 --> 14:11.400
Me, I got a lot of
time for Bruce Beetham.

14:11.520 --> 14:15.840
[laughing]

14:15.960 --> 14:17.400
Good to see you back, Ted.

14:17.520 --> 14:18.560
Never went anywhere, Mike.

14:26.040 --> 14:27.880
[car engine starts]

14:28.000 --> 14:29.360
Shooting through, pet?

14:29.480 --> 14:31.320
Yes, Ted, I am.

14:31.440 --> 14:32.800
A pity.

14:32.920 --> 14:34.200
Nice of you to look
after Rita, though.

14:34.320 --> 14:35.120
Ah, it's my pleasure.

14:38.920 --> 14:40.760
What did he want?

14:40.880 --> 14:43.080
Probably best you don'twear that broach for a while.

14:43.200 --> 14:44.560
I think I can manage that.

14:44.680 --> 14:48.040
[car starts]

14:48.160 --> 14:49.320
All right, boy.

14:49.440 --> 14:50.960
Let's go see these people.- Forget them.

14:51.080 --> 14:52.320
No, no.

14:52.440 --> 14:53.560
He needs to put
right what he's done.

